VALUES ('e8bacb87-d388-4525-b03c-afb4bd70d53a', 'Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?', 'The monograph''s central term—enjambment, a coinage its author, a notoriously precise stylist, defended at length—anchors the argument ______ that the later commentators, working from an abridged edition, persistently misread.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":", a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"B","text":"; a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Run-on] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"C","text":": a claim","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the boundary correctly attaches the non-restrictive appositive without splicing the clause."},{"id":"D","text":" a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Logical Reconstruction:
Step 1: Locate the main clause and the trailing modifier across nested appositives.
Step 2: Distinguish a restrictive from a non-restrictive reading of the appositive.
Step 3: Reject marks that create a comma splice or run-on.
Step 4: Only the correct mark closes the parenthetical and joins the clauses.

Key Explanation: Choice C is the only option whose second sentence survives the discriminating step above; the others are grounded in real passage language but fail a specific qualifier.

Distractor Analysis:
- Choice A [Comma Splice]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence imports a relationship the passage withholds — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice B [Run-on]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence satisfies only part of the stated condition — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice D [Restrictive/Non-Restrictive]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence extends beyond the passage''s qualifiers — exactly the habit this trap exploits.

Difficulty Justification: This item is Challenge-tier because of restrictive/non-restrictive appositive discrimination under simultaneously nested punctuation.

Score Prediction: A student scoring 750+ on DSAT R&W should answer this item correctly with deliberate reasoning; a student scoring 720–740 should find it genuinely difficult even after a careful first pass.', NULL, 'Standard English Conventions', 'Boundaries', 'reading_writing', 'conventions', 'BOU', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"tier":"challenge","challenge_tier":true,"challenged_problem":true,"difficulty_tier":"challenge","explanation_v2":true,"generator":"generate-challenge-bank.mjs","rw_subtype":"boundaries","rw_format":"grammar_blank","challenge_key":"BOU"}'::jsonb, true, now(), now());
